        <h2>Topic: Exponential Growth</h2>
        <p>Exponential growth happens when a quantity increases by a constant factor over equal time intervals.</p>
        <p>Example: If a population doubles every year, then starting with 100:</p>
        <p><strong>Year 1: 200, Year 2: 400, Year 3: 800</strong></p>
